<item>
            <title>[SPARK-27575] Spark overwrites existing value of spark.yarn.dist.* instead of merging value</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-27575</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If we specify `--files` arg when submitting app where configuration has &quot;spark.yarn.dist.files&quot;, SparkSubmit overwrites the new files (files provided in arg) instead of merging existing value in configuration.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Same&#160;issue happens&#160;also on &quot;spark.yarn.dist.pyFiles&quot;, &quot;spark.yarn.dist.jars&quot;, &quot;spark.yarn.dist.archives&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;While I encountered the issue in Spark 2.4.0, I can see&#160;the issue from codebase in&#160;master branch and also branch-2.3 as well.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
